\pard\s3\sb100\sa100 List Surgeries/Treatments:\par
Biopsy \par
A procedure that involves obtaining a tissue specimen for microscopic analysis to establish a precise diagnosis\par
Biopsy shave \par
A procedure in which a skin abnormality and a thin layer of surrounding skin are removed with a small blade for examination under a microscope. Stitches are not needed with this procedure.\par
Curettage \par
The removal of tissue or growths from a body cavity by scraping with a curette\par
Incision and drainage \par
Incision is the cutting of or into body tissues.\par
Drainage is the removal of fluid or purulent material from a wound, sore or cavity.\par
Skin grafting and flap \par
A skin graft is a patch of skin that is surgically removed from one area of the body and transplanted to another area.\par
Surgical Excision \par
Surgical Excision refers to \ldblquote cutting\rdblquote  out of a skin lesion (growth). Some of the commonest lesions which are excised are moles, cysts and xanthelasma (cholesterol deposits).\par
Electrosurgery\par
Electrosurgery is the use of an electric device for removing small superficial skin growths, such as viral warts, seborrhoeic keratoses (age growths) and skin tags.\par
Mohs Micrographic Surgery for Skin Cancers Micrographic (Mohs\rquote ) surgery\~\par
Mohs surgery (MMS) is a surgical service for skin cancer patients. The procedure involves the excision of abnormal tissue in successive layers and microscopically scanning the entire under surface of each layer by the systematic use of horizontally-cut frozen sections.\par
List of Specialties /Departments:\par
Medlite C6\'99 Laser Treatment\par
This laser is used to treat hypopigmented skin problems such as vitiligo, pale scars and stretchmarks.\par
MiXto SX CO2 Fractional Laser Treatment \par
MiXto SX Fractional CO2 laser can be used to smooth out lines, wrinkles and scars, remove brown spots and other irregularities, and to tighten the skin. This technique makes the healing process much faster and enables a patient to get back to normal activities sooner.\par
Filler Injection / Sculptra (Poly-L-lactic acid) \par
Fillers are purified substances injected into skin to improve the appearance of deep lines, provide fullness or correct depressed scars.\par
Botulinum Toxin \par
Botulinum toxin is a purified protein injection to cause temporary weakening of the muscle. It is used to reduce dynamic wrinkles such frown lines, crow's feet as well as excessive sweatiness of the underarms.\~\par
Carbon Dioxide Laser Treatment \par
This can be used to precisely remove unwanted skin growths such as syringomas and to resurface scars and wrinkles.\~\par
Cellular grafting for Vitiligo\par
Non-cultured cellular grafting is an innovative surgical technique that transplants an individual\rquote s own pigment cells onto his / her vitiligo patches, without the need of growing the cells in the laboratory.\par
Chemical Peels\par
Chemical peeling may improve skin texture as well as mild acne, superficial wrinkles and scars.\~\par
Intense Pulsed Light (IPL)\par
A broad band light source which can be used to treat certain pigmented and red skin lesions such as. freckles, age spots, melasma and facial redness.\~\par
Laser Hair Removal \par
Laser hair removal is a safe, relatively painless and effective way of removing unwanted hair. The long-pulsed Nd-YAG laser is safe for use in darker Asian skin colour types.\~\par
Mole Removal \par
There are different types of moles and method of removal varies. Moles can be removed either by surgery or by laser treatment.\~\par
Pigment Laser Treatment \par
Q-switched Pigment lasers can be used to treat freckles, age spots, Hori's naevus, tattoos, and certain birthmarks such as naevus of Ota and caf\'e9-au-lait macules.\~\~\par
Pulsed Dye Laser Treatment \par
The pulsed dye laser such as the V-Beam is used to treat vascular skin lesions such as portwine stains, superficial haemangiomas, fine facial and leg veins and to reduce redness in young scars.\par
Smoothbeam Diode Laser Treatment\par
Smoothbeam diode laser have been developed to directly stimulate collagen synthesis without damaging the outermost layer of skin.\par
V Beam Laser Treatment \par
The V Beam laser can be used to treat portwine stains, infantile haemangiomas, telangiectasias and hypertrophic scars.\par
